	"description": "Smart contracts are like digital agreements that run on blockchain technology,\nmaking transactions automatic and secure. While many people use Ethereum and\nSolidity to create these contracts, there are other options that can be just as\npowerful. \n\nOne great combination is using Rust with the Gear Protocol. In this guide, I&#x27;ll\nshow you how to build and deploy a smart contract using Rust and the Gear\nProtocol. Whether you&#x27;re new to this or have some experience, this article will\nhelp you get start",
